.TH "fsverity_hash_page" 9 "fsverity_hash_page" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fsverity_hash_page \- hash a single data or hash page
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" fsverity_hash_page
.BI "(const struct merkle_tree_params *params "  ","
.BI "const struct inode *inode "  ","
.BI "struct ahash_request *req "  ","
.BI "struct page *page "  ","
.BI "u8 *out "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "params" 12
the Merkle tree's parameters
.IP "inode" 12
inode for which the hashing is being done
.IP "req" 12
preallocated hash request
.IP "page" 12
the page to hash
.IP "out" 12
output digest, size 'params->digest_size' bytes
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Hash a single data or hash block, assuming block_size == PAGE_SIZE.
The hash is salted if a salt is specified in the Merkle tree parameters.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, -errno on failure
